_aChangeLog.text: Redid several indoors areas with static props mismatching with nav, also at both bombsites
Removed/changed several tiles (poles at A, Alley; sheet metal "doorway" at Side) that were impassable
Removed jumping in doorways and on Bridge
Fixed bathroom accessibility on both sides
Removed impossible dropdowns near Bridge (which I think got some bots stuck), also on fenced area on Alley-BackAlley border
Some minor place name changes ("Downstairs" renamed "Family Room", fixed some odd borders between areas)
some tile shape changes in various areas

_aLatestUpdates._sText:
Most of these changes should definitely be improvements, two minor ones I'm not sure about:

- a pipe of sorts in the ground at B near the sewer ladder that you have to jump onto or across. Might have been better to have the nav avoid it entirely. Previously made a bigger gap in the net than it probably should even then.

- While a lot of the props nav previously went right through the bottom of are solid (like Washing Machines, Stoves), I also put some tiles on top of tables... at least some of which I later noticed are destructible. Might revert this in a later update if it turns out to have been stupid.

_sText:
[v1.0] This is pretty basic right now, I had a very autogenerated-looking nav around (the map source for de_shanty / "de_shanty_v3" is a nice map but comes just with bsp) and did some pretty superficial improvements for the time being to make it less terrible:

- added place names (32 of them in total)
- removed inaccessible areas (probably just regenerating to not have this would have been easier, but I noticed too late...)
- made ladders accessible
- fixed some broken staircases
- added missing connections over aboveground scrap metal walkways (most of "Roof", part of "Loft", all of "Deck" and "Bridge")
- broke up and merged some particularly hideous tiles (but no deep optimization or anything)
- removed some blatantly bad jumps and dropdowns

There's one weird thing on this map, some big wooden doors that the nav generator seems to believe are breakable, and I've managed to break one of them... but with a ton of hits. It doesn't seem worth keeping these as connections (except for the different breakable wall near "Bathroom" and A), but not 100% sure if completely removing these was really the right idea.
